      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MONTY MONTE (2) ran third last start at Melton over 2240m, beaten 23 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Taking on a better field but he is good enough to cope. TINEY (3) led at his most recent outing and was successful in a nice return to form at this track over 2230m, getting home by 6 metres. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Steps up a level but he is capable of running another big race. TRANQUIL BILL (5) is the next best after finishing runner-up over 2230m at this track last time out. PERSEVERANSE (1) will be rock-hard fit after four runs back from a spell, the latest effort a third at this track a week ago.",
